[{"type":"p","props":{"children":["This plugin does expose Plone content hierarchy in Gatsby GraphQL queries directly. Each folderish content node will contain a special ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["nodes"]}}," attribute, which links to children for that node (GraphQLUnionType). In addition, each node will also  contain a special attribute ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["_path"]}}," describing the position of node in content hierarchy. Container nodes will contain ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["_path"]}}," attribute also for each item in its ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["items"]}}," attribute returned by Plone REST API."]}},{"type":"p","props":{"children":["In ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["./demo"]}},", use of ",{"type":"code","props":{"children":["_path"]}}," is illustrated for instance, in the ",{"type":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/collective/gatsby-source-plone/blob/master/demo/src/components/Folder.js","children":["Folder component"]}},", where details of it's children are retrieved:"]}},{"type":"pre","props":{"children":[{"type":"code","props":{"className":"language-graphql","children":["fragment Folder on PloneFolder {
  id
  title
  description
  items {
    _id
    _path
    _type
    description
    title
  }
  _path
}"]}}]}}]
